WEBVTT

01:26.900 --> 01:35.030
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

01:35.420 --> 01:37.729
[Episode 11]

01:40.180 --> 01:40.910
Shen Ranran,

01:41.150 --> 01:42.009
you have a call!

01:42.900 --> 01:45.830
-Maybe calling about when I join the crew.
-Go ahead.

01:50.450 --> 01:50.850
Hello?

01:52.590 --> 01:53.590
Mr. Cui, go ahead.

01:54.700 --> 01:55.229
Ranran,

01:55.950 --> 01:57.550
I have something to tell you.

01:58.000 --> 01:59.310
I'm at your beck and call.

01:59.310 --> 02:00.570
Whatever you say goes.

02:02.780 --> 02:03.180
Hello?

02:05.510 --> 02:05.930
Hello?

02:07.340 --> 02:07.800
Ranran,

02:08.340 --> 02:09.340
here's the thing.

02:10.210 --> 02:13.210
You know how unpredictable
the weather can be, right?

02:13.870 --> 02:14.930
Is it going to rain?

02:16.870 --> 02:17.640
No.

02:19.680 --> 02:21.079
I don't see any rain here.

02:21.650 --> 02:23.579
I don't even know what to say to you.

02:24.030 --> 02:25.940
I mean, some things

02:26.020 --> 02:28.280
don't always turn out the way you expect.

02:28.310 --> 02:29.640
There could be changes.

02:30.690 --> 02:33.090
I'm not getting
the third female lead role?

02:34.750 --> 02:35.380
It's okay.

02:36.130 --> 02:37.650
Fourth, fifth, or sixth lead,

02:37.650 --> 02:40.370
featured extra, or even just an extra—
I can do it.

02:40.370 --> 02:40.829
Ranran,

02:41.130 --> 02:42.260
don't get worked up.

02:43.060 --> 02:44.790
I'll just be straight with you.

02:44.970 --> 02:46.690
Your role as the third female lead

02:46.690 --> 02:48.420
has been given to someone else.

02:51.620 --> 02:54.400
I... got replaced?

02:54.590 --> 02:55.180
Yes.

02:55.270 --> 02:57.400
All the other roles have been cast too.

02:58.340 --> 02:59.740
You can't be in this show.

03:01.340 --> 03:03.280
Ranran? Ranran?

03:10.560 --> 03:11.310
Mr. Cui.

03:11.710 --> 03:12.710
Mr. Cui, please talk to the director.

03:12.710 --> 03:13.520
I will do my best

03:13.520 --> 03:14.120
in this role.

03:14.120 --> 03:14.780
It's not about

03:14.780 --> 03:16.710
whether you can play the part well.

03:16.960 --> 03:17.500
But...

03:17.780 --> 03:18.750
they'd already decided that role was mine.

03:18.750 --> 03:19.860
How can they just replace me?

03:19.860 --> 03:20.530
How would I know?

03:20.530 --> 03:23.130
Someone came out of nowhere
and took your role!

03:23.150 --> 03:24.610
I want to see the director.

03:26.840 --> 03:28.430
Why go see the director?

03:28.910 --> 03:30.910
You'd only put him in an awkward spot.

03:30.910 --> 03:31.890
No matter what,

03:32.340 --> 03:34.000
I have to talk to the director.

03:34.130 --> 03:35.860
I need to show him my sincerity.

03:36.460 --> 03:37.530
If the director could make the call,

03:37.530 --> 03:39.460
he would've kept you, wouldn't he?

03:41.810 --> 03:43.150
Then what should I do now?

03:43.150 --> 03:44.079
How would I know?

03:47.300 --> 03:49.360
This kind of thing happens every day.

03:50.030 --> 03:51.030
In this industry,

03:51.340 --> 03:52.600
without connections,

03:52.750 --> 03:54.300
you really won't get anywhere.

03:54.300 --> 03:56.630
But I didn't have any connections before,

03:57.250 --> 03:58.470
and I still got the role.

03:58.470 --> 03:59.329
Did you really?

03:59.840 --> 04:01.030
You just got replaced, didn't you?

04:01.030 --> 04:01.690
Didn't you?

04:05.180 --> 04:06.190
Don't... Don't...

04:06.190 --> 04:07.250
Don't... don't...

04:07.300 --> 04:09.000
Don't cry. Don't cry. Alright.

04:09.000 --> 04:09.460
Well...

04:12.340 --> 04:13.200
How about this?

04:13.680 --> 04:14.880
The biggest investor

04:15.150 --> 04:16.010
in this show

04:16.010 --> 04:16.829
is Mr. Chu.

04:17.769 --> 04:18.430
I'm actually

04:18.430 --> 04:19.829
on decent enough terms with him.

04:19.829 --> 04:21.370
He's somebody in the industry too.

04:21.370 --> 04:22.570
I'll see if I can

04:22.680 --> 04:23.690
introduce you to each other.

04:23.690 --> 04:24.820
If this works out...

04:25.430 --> 04:26.560
it's your last shot.

04:29.040 --> 04:29.620
Okay?

04:31.450 --> 04:34.400
[Seasons Change Hostel]

04:33.130 --> 04:34.659
Is that investor reliable?

04:36.040 --> 04:36.790
I don't know.

04:37.770 --> 04:39.500
What's that investor's name?

04:41.920 --> 04:44.300
His name is... Chu Caiyuan.

04:47.830 --> 04:48.240
Okay.

04:48.810 --> 04:49.570
Later,

04:49.690 --> 04:51.800
I'll ask around
with the assistant directors I know

04:51.800 --> 04:52.870
about this guy.

04:54.070 --> 04:54.570
Right.

04:55.270 --> 04:56.770
I can also ask around the crew

04:56.770 --> 04:58.310
to see what that investor is like too.

04:58.310 --> 04:58.690
Okay.

04:59.180 --> 05:01.130
Beijing is huge.
There are all sorts of people here.

05:01.130 --> 05:03.410
It doesn't matter what kind of man he is!

05:03.920 --> 05:04.670
Just go!

05:05.130 --> 05:06.740
See what tricks he can pull!

05:07.980 --> 05:09.450
But I've never been to

05:09.480 --> 05:10.310
that kind of occasion.

05:10.310 --> 05:11.570
I don't know what to do.

05:11.870 --> 05:13.130
I really don't want to go.

05:13.130 --> 05:13.980
But if I don't,

05:14.000 --> 05:14.540
I have no idea

05:14.540 --> 05:16.600
when the next opportunity will come.

05:18.680 --> 05:20.110
If you should go, then go,

05:20.220 --> 05:20.690
right?

05:20.830 --> 05:22.300
Introduce yourself

05:22.360 --> 05:23.270
when it's time.

05:24.800 --> 05:25.930
Hold your head high,

05:25.950 --> 05:26.430
right?

05:27.040 --> 05:27.970
We shouldn't

05:28.190 --> 05:29.060
bow or scrape.

05:29.430 --> 05:30.430
Zongbao is right.

05:31.000 --> 05:32.220
Just be natural about it.

05:32.220 --> 05:32.820
It's okay.

05:32.870 --> 05:33.480
Exactly.

05:33.630 --> 05:35.400
Don't imagine the worst.

05:35.740 --> 05:37.270
It might actually be a good opportunity.

05:37.270 --> 05:37.670
Right.

05:38.370 --> 05:39.430
If he really tries to
pull something on us,

05:39.430 --> 05:40.430
we can just leave.

05:40.450 --> 05:41.450
There are plenty of other chances.

05:41.450 --> 05:41.860
Yeah.

05:42.360 --> 05:43.330
Don't be afraid.

05:43.930 --> 05:45.240
Even if the sky falls,

05:45.720 --> 05:46.810
just tell me.

05:47.220 --> 05:48.280
I've got your back.

05:49.510 --> 05:50.040
And me.

05:51.920 --> 05:52.630
Anyway, wherever

05:52.630 --> 05:53.430
you need me,

05:53.450 --> 05:54.360
whether it's physical labor

05:54.360 --> 05:55.360
or anything else,

05:55.360 --> 05:56.240
just say the word.

05:56.240 --> 05:57.830
I won't hesitate for a second.

05:57.830 --> 05:58.290
Ranran,

05:59.450 --> 06:00.780
no matter what happens,

06:01.250 --> 06:02.710
as long as we keep smiling,

06:02.810 --> 06:03.800
we haven't lost.

06:04.570 --> 06:05.220
We've all

06:05.240 --> 06:06.630
got your back.

06:07.060 --> 06:07.460
Right.

06:09.000 --> 06:10.000
What do you think?

06:10.980 --> 06:11.370
Fine.

06:12.570 --> 06:13.330
I'll go.

06:13.950 --> 06:15.570
I believe I'm a good actress.

06:16.310 --> 06:17.250
I am the unbreakable

06:17.250 --> 06:17.980
Wu Qinghua!

06:18.630 --> 06:19.480
I can do this.

06:19.720 --> 06:20.810
You definitely can!

06:20.810 --> 06:21.940
You definitely can!

06:26.810 --> 06:27.770
If that big investor

06:27.770 --> 06:28.600
rubs you the wrong way,

06:28.600 --> 06:29.930
come back immediately.

06:31.430 --> 06:32.360
Don't drink.

06:33.270 --> 06:35.670
Just say you're
taking care of your health.

06:35.810 --> 06:36.180
Okay.

06:43.370 --> 06:43.920
Mr. Zhou!

06:44.430 --> 06:45.560
Yes, it's me, Cao Ye!

06:46.890 --> 06:47.550
No problem!

06:47.600 --> 06:48.180
I'm free!

06:48.190 --> 06:49.590
I can head over right now!

06:50.000 --> 06:51.040
It's about my paintings, right?

06:51.040 --> 06:52.040
They sold, right?

06:53.310 --> 06:54.240
Okay, okay.

06:54.330 --> 06:55.250
Let's talk details in person.

06:55.250 --> 06:55.580
Okay.

07:00.950 --> 07:01.720
Good news?

07:05.600 --> 07:06.740
Wait for me to come back.

07:06.740 --> 07:08.030
Pick any restaurant you want,

07:08.030 --> 07:08.560
my treat.

07:09.010 --> 07:10.270
A fortune is coming in.

07:10.420 --> 07:11.810
Fortune or not, it's all just

07:11.810 --> 07:12.890
worldly possessions, right?

07:12.890 --> 07:13.430
Can you use

07:13.430 --> 07:14.330
those worldly possessions

07:14.330 --> 07:15.930
to pay the rent you owe first?

07:16.190 --> 07:17.310
They're not in my possession yet.

07:17.310 --> 07:18.250
Wait until I get back.

07:18.250 --> 07:19.390
Forget about the overdue rent,

07:19.390 --> 07:21.250
I'll pay for a whole year upfront!

07:21.750 --> 07:22.810
See? What did I say?

07:23.480 --> 07:25.810
You're never meant to
stay in a small pond.

07:26.010 --> 07:26.870
Let me teach you one more time.

07:26.870 --> 07:27.870
Keep this in mind.

07:28.220 --> 07:30.680
A golden-scaled fish was never meant to
stay in a pond;

07:30.680 --> 07:33.250
when the winds and clouds stir,
it transforms into a dragon!

07:33.250 --> 07:34.850
You've turned into a dragon!

07:35.600 --> 07:37.260
I'm going to my room to change.

07:37.300 --> 07:38.560
You, help me hail a cab.

07:38.720 --> 07:40.520
We're moving up in the world now!

07:41.220 --> 07:42.820
Help me pay for the cab first.

07:43.750 --> 07:45.680
I'll pay you double when I get back.

07:46.270 --> 07:47.000
Got it!

07:49.100 --> 07:50.190
This was the expert dorm

07:50.190 --> 07:51.240
back at our studio.

07:51.240 --> 07:51.750
Director Weng,

07:51.750 --> 07:53.409
would such a master accept me?

07:53.720 --> 07:54.810
We're already here.

07:54.810 --> 07:56.010
Don't talk nonsense.

07:56.740 --> 07:57.860
Let me put it this way.

07:57.860 --> 07:58.890
I think

07:59.000 --> 08:00.460
your handwriting is good.

08:00.860 --> 08:02.190
It might catch his eye.

08:03.690 --> 08:05.220
It's also because you've got it on you.

08:05.220 --> 08:06.060
If you were no good,

08:06.060 --> 08:08.320
I'd be too embarrassed to recommend you.

08:08.420 --> 08:10.010
Let me say the hard part first.

08:10.010 --> 08:11.270
Hello, Director Weng.

08:12.620 --> 08:14.280
Let me say the hard part first.

08:15.740 --> 08:17.540
Whether it goes well or not

08:18.450 --> 08:19.430
depends on you.

08:20.000 --> 08:20.800
Don't worry.

08:20.830 --> 08:21.800
I'll do whatever it takes

08:21.800 --> 08:22.660
to get him to take me on.

08:22.660 --> 08:22.990
Good.

08:27.180 --> 08:28.920
There're scissors, glue,

08:29.130 --> 08:30.160
and carbon paper in here.

08:30.160 --> 08:31.130
I've prepared everything

08:31.130 --> 08:31.990
I could for you.

08:32.340 --> 08:34.400
These are tools I used back in the day.

08:35.440 --> 08:36.900
Thank you, Director Weng.

08:38.980 --> 08:39.500
Listen,

08:39.530 --> 08:41.150
if he does take you on,

08:41.650 --> 08:43.200
you must learn from him properly.

08:43.200 --> 08:44.660
Definitely. Definitely.

08:59.340 --> 08:59.810
See?

09:00.510 --> 09:03.120
Sleeping in broad daylight
with the door unlocked.

09:03.120 --> 09:04.980
He's waiting to swindle someone.

09:11.100 --> 09:11.630
I was just

09:12.250 --> 09:14.980
dreaming about a key plot point
for the script...

09:20.750 --> 09:22.100
and you woke me up.

09:22.980 --> 09:25.180
I don't care! I've brought the man here!

09:25.460 --> 09:26.520
I won't see you out.

09:29.960 --> 09:30.620
No, wait...

09:30.870 --> 09:31.530
You stay...

09:37.960 --> 09:38.820
Hello, mentor.

09:39.600 --> 09:40.800
My name is Xu Shengli.

09:40.940 --> 09:41.870
Xu, spelled X-U.

09:41.960 --> 09:43.550
Shengli as in "Shengli Oilfield."

09:43.550 --> 09:44.210
Okay, okay.

09:45.120 --> 09:46.870
Don't give me that whole spiel.

10:25.150 --> 10:26.480
How does it smell to you?

10:27.220 --> 10:28.600
The stink of alcohol, eh?

10:28.600 --> 10:30.330
It's the fragrance of alcohol.

10:32.910 --> 10:34.240
A sweet-talking man...

10:35.360 --> 10:38.120
I'd better watch out for you.

10:43.840 --> 10:45.700
It smells rough but tastes great.

10:48.130 --> 10:49.630
Good, good.

10:51.270 --> 10:53.270
You've smoothed things over.

10:56.580 --> 10:59.320
I can't find anything
to criticize about you, huh?

10:59.320 --> 11:00.370
Go! Get out!

11:00.600 --> 11:02.340
Get out! Go! Get out!

11:02.770 --> 11:03.830
Mr... Mr. He, um...

11:12.150 --> 11:13.430
Coming, coming.

11:13.940 --> 11:14.610
Wait a second!

11:14.610 --> 11:15.670
Wait, wait.

11:15.980 --> 11:18.320
Come on, hurry, come back and sit!

11:18.340 --> 11:19.580
Hurry! Come on and sit!

11:19.580 --> 11:20.580
Sit! Sit down!

11:20.860 --> 11:21.580
Pen, pen.

11:21.720 --> 11:22.320
Come here.

11:23.220 --> 11:24.440
Sit here! Here!

11:24.580 --> 11:25.240
Right here!

11:25.870 --> 11:26.600
Take the pen.

11:26.860 --> 11:28.460
I'll dictate, and you write.

11:28.700 --> 11:30.600
Hurry up! Hurry!

11:31.200 --> 11:32.600
An abandoned factory...

11:32.600 --> 11:34.000
An abandoned factory...

11:34.480 --> 11:36.320
Night. Summer, summer.

11:35.780 --> 11:38.060
[An abandoned factory, night, summer]

11:38.650 --> 11:41.530
Dark clouds... cover the moon.

11:43.440 --> 11:45.980
The wind howls,

11:44.270 --> 11:48.310
[The clouds cover the moon. The wind.]

11:46.790 --> 11:49.220
and the leaves shake violently.

11:50.080 --> 11:50.880
Write faster.

11:51.220 --> 11:52.390
Shake violently...

11:53.320 --> 11:54.310
At this moment,

11:54.360 --> 11:55.090
suddenly...

11:56.620 --> 11:59.870
a little stray cat appears.

12:00.170 --> 12:00.960
Mr. He, could you

12:00.960 --> 12:01.910
speak a little slower?

12:01.910 --> 12:03.440
You need to write faster!

12:03.620 --> 12:04.550
You... you're speaking Sichuan dialect,

12:04.550 --> 12:05.840
and I... I need time to process it.

12:05.840 --> 12:06.530
Sichuan dialect?

12:06.530 --> 12:08.170
I'm speaking Mandarin!

12:09.460 --> 12:10.320
Where were you?

12:11.130 --> 12:12.740
I wrote to wind... leaves... wind...

12:12.740 --> 12:13.120
To...

12:13.250 --> 12:14.740
A little stray cat appears!

12:14.740 --> 12:16.980
A little stray cat... a little stray cat.

12:16.980 --> 12:18.310
The little stray cat...

12:19.050 --> 12:23.010
tiptoes into the factory building.

12:23.460 --> 12:26.510
Shadows flicker across the building.

12:26.700 --> 12:27.960
Suddenly, a scream!

12:30.720 --> 12:32.300
Who moved my chair,

12:32.360 --> 12:32.750
huh?

12:33.340 --> 12:33.770
Who?

12:33.840 --> 12:34.480
I... I...

12:34.530 --> 12:35.500
I moved it over just now.

12:35.500 --> 12:36.170
I thought I'd sit there.

12:36.170 --> 12:37.100
Move it back!

12:37.150 --> 12:38.990
Move it back for me! Move it back!

12:41.750 --> 12:42.560
Move it back!

12:44.510 --> 12:45.020
Right.

12:45.150 --> 12:47.250
Don't let it happen again.

12:48.600 --> 12:49.840
Sit back. Sit.

12:53.860 --> 12:55.180
For us screenwriters,

12:55.460 --> 12:57.650
the most important thing is inspiration.

12:57.650 --> 12:59.440
Inspiration is like a ghost.

13:00.720 --> 13:02.450
You don't know when it will come

13:02.740 --> 13:04.340
or when it will leave.

13:04.790 --> 13:05.650
It's fleeting.

13:05.790 --> 13:06.920
You have to catch it.

13:09.120 --> 13:10.320
On this desk

13:10.500 --> 13:12.410
are the scripts I wrote.

13:12.960 --> 13:14.940
They are part of my creation.

13:17.870 --> 13:18.650
My...

13:19.890 --> 13:21.550
my eyes are always so worn out.

13:22.630 --> 13:23.570
So I need someone

13:23.860 --> 13:25.320
to help me copy my scripts.

13:25.630 --> 13:27.090
Your handwriting is nice.

13:27.750 --> 13:29.120
I think you'll be of use.

13:30.790 --> 13:33.190
Since you're going to work here,

13:33.510 --> 13:34.990
first of all,

13:35.630 --> 13:37.170
let's set the ground rules.

13:37.910 --> 13:38.530
First,

13:40.240 --> 13:41.660
in this room,

13:41.960 --> 13:43.060
nothing

13:43.720 --> 13:44.700
can be touched.

13:45.480 --> 13:47.410
Don't move anything, even an inch.

13:47.460 --> 13:48.260
Do you hear me?

13:48.600 --> 13:48.940
Okay.

13:49.340 --> 13:50.220
Second...

13:52.200 --> 13:53.370
Pour me a cup of water.

13:53.370 --> 13:54.570
Pour me a cup of water.

13:56.290 --> 13:56.740
Right.

13:58.150 --> 13:58.620
Over there.

13:58.620 --> 13:59.890
Yes, there. That's it.

14:00.500 --> 14:01.560
Pour me some water.

14:07.000 --> 14:09.120
-An abandoned factory...
-Mr. He, water.

14:09.120 --> 14:09.520
Water.

14:09.890 --> 14:11.530
This is the second rule.

14:12.750 --> 14:14.980
When I wake up,

14:15.790 --> 14:17.420
you pour me a cup of water.

14:17.620 --> 14:18.480
Okay, got it.

14:18.960 --> 14:20.100
Sit down. Sit.

14:20.360 --> 14:20.790
Sit.

14:28.410 --> 14:29.240
And third,

14:30.100 --> 14:30.770
you have to

14:31.080 --> 14:32.030
stay

14:32.220 --> 14:33.500
in this room all day.

14:34.770 --> 14:36.440
You can only leave

14:36.530 --> 14:37.680
when I say so.

14:38.080 --> 14:38.810
Understand?

14:38.840 --> 14:40.300
Understand, understand.

14:40.440 --> 14:42.290
So I'll be here all day?

14:43.440 --> 14:45.770
Then w-will you provide three meals a day?

14:46.940 --> 14:47.620
You idiot.

14:48.460 --> 14:49.790
This isn't a cafeteria.

14:50.510 --> 14:52.250
I only cover lunch.

14:52.370 --> 14:53.030
No problem.

14:53.100 --> 14:54.700
I'd do it even without meals.

14:56.170 --> 14:57.010
Let me tell you

14:57.250 --> 14:58.650
how to handle newcomers.

14:58.770 --> 14:59.680
Newcomers

14:59.750 --> 15:01.350
are like grass in the spring.

15:02.200 --> 15:03.030
You never know

15:03.030 --> 15:04.270
which sprout will bloom

15:04.270 --> 15:05.370
and which won't.

15:05.750 --> 15:06.320
So,

15:06.460 --> 15:07.960
you have to give them more sunshine

15:07.960 --> 15:09.090
and water them more.

15:09.290 --> 15:10.270
When the spring breeze blows,

15:10.270 --> 15:11.730
you'll know immediately.

15:13.080 --> 15:13.480
What?

15:13.940 --> 15:15.620
What are sunshine and water?

15:16.630 --> 15:17.340
Money!

15:18.550 --> 15:19.630
Investment!

15:21.670 --> 15:22.100
Right.

15:22.480 --> 15:24.530
Our money is the sunshine

15:24.550 --> 15:25.320
and water.

15:25.770 --> 15:26.700
Who are we?

15:26.980 --> 15:28.180
We're the investors.

15:30.250 --> 15:31.050
Let's do this—

15:31.200 --> 15:32.000
once you've picked the actors,

15:32.000 --> 15:32.930
bring them to me.

15:33.150 --> 15:34.350
I'll vet them for you.

15:37.080 --> 15:37.620
You're here!

15:37.620 --> 15:38.130
Mr. Chu,

15:38.370 --> 15:39.980
really, I haven't even
had a proper word with you yet,

15:39.980 --> 15:40.440
and you've

15:40.440 --> 15:41.840
already enlightened me.

15:42.740 --> 15:44.250
Not at all. That was a friend of mine.

15:44.250 --> 15:45.500
He wants to invest in film and TV too.

15:45.500 --> 15:47.500
I was just giving him some pointers.

15:49.290 --> 15:50.480
Let me introduce you.

15:50.480 --> 15:50.940
Ranran,

15:51.080 --> 15:51.550
this is

15:51.600 --> 15:52.900
the famous Mr. Chu.

15:53.120 --> 15:53.580
Mr. Chu,

15:53.840 --> 15:54.530
this is the actress

15:54.530 --> 15:55.690
I mentioned before—

15:55.820 --> 15:56.550
Shen Ranran.

15:58.030 --> 15:59.720
Okay. Good, good.

16:02.670 --> 16:04.330
Well, don't just stand there.

16:04.580 --> 16:05.310
Let's go eat.

16:06.170 --> 16:06.630
Mr. Chu,

16:06.670 --> 16:07.650
I'm really sorry.

16:07.650 --> 16:09.290
I thought we'd just chat for a bit.

16:09.290 --> 16:10.030
In a little while,

16:10.030 --> 16:12.010
I have to go pick up a relative
at the train station.

16:12.010 --> 16:12.470
Well...

16:13.080 --> 16:13.610
Why don't

16:14.080 --> 16:15.810
you two go ahead and have lunch?

16:21.860 --> 16:22.440
Shen,

16:23.010 --> 16:24.070
where are you from?

16:24.200 --> 16:24.750
Huzhou.

16:26.080 --> 16:27.210
You're from Huzhou.

16:27.720 --> 16:28.980
Huzhou is a nice place.

16:30.340 --> 16:30.940
Waitress,

16:31.720 --> 16:33.410
do you have any Huzhou cuisine here?

16:33.410 --> 16:33.870
Sir,

16:33.910 --> 16:35.170
at the Siji Kang Grand Hotel,

16:35.170 --> 16:36.480
you can find dishes
from all over the country.

16:36.480 --> 16:37.630
Talk is cheap.

16:39.410 --> 16:40.340
I'm telling you,

16:40.460 --> 16:41.590
this guest next to me

16:41.870 --> 16:42.730
is from Huzhou.

16:42.910 --> 16:43.820
I want to know

16:44.270 --> 16:45.200
if your dishes

16:45.620 --> 16:46.480
are authentic.

16:46.910 --> 16:47.770
If they're not,

16:48.150 --> 16:49.010
I'm not paying.

16:51.220 --> 16:52.320
It's my honor to invite you here

16:52.320 --> 16:53.180
for a meal.

16:53.390 --> 16:55.190
Please order whatever you like.

16:55.600 --> 16:56.460
Don't say that.

16:56.510 --> 16:57.440
It's just a meal.

16:57.910 --> 16:58.680
Besides,

16:59.010 --> 17:00.140
for actors like you,

17:00.200 --> 17:02.130
it's not easy making it in Beijing.

17:03.250 --> 17:03.970
Well,

17:04.220 --> 17:05.109
I'd like

17:05.109 --> 17:06.349
a Stewed Shredded Eel.

17:06.349 --> 17:07.480
I want the eel to be freshly killed.

17:07.480 --> 17:09.140
Have Chef Liu make it himself.

17:09.510 --> 17:10.300
Then...

17:10.440 --> 17:12.040
a serving of Tofu Skin Rolls.

17:12.220 --> 17:14.150
A Drunken Fish and Crispy Pork Pot.

17:14.510 --> 17:15.790
Do you have any Choy Sum in season today?

17:15.790 --> 17:16.089
Yes.

17:16.660 --> 17:17.460
That's great.

17:18.109 --> 17:19.400
These hutong alleys are so winding.

17:19.400 --> 17:20.440
Where on earth is this place?

17:20.440 --> 17:22.099
You're living so deep inside.

17:22.980 --> 17:24.000
Are we there yet?

17:25.920 --> 17:26.900
Are we there yet?

17:29.980 --> 17:31.090
Where? Here?

17:31.900 --> 17:32.920
You should've said something.

17:32.920 --> 17:33.880
I was still pedaling forward!

17:33.880 --> 17:35.140
You're unbelievable.

17:35.530 --> 17:36.180
Making this little bit of money off you

17:36.180 --> 17:37.510
is hard work, honestly.

17:38.270 --> 17:39.050
My goodness.

17:40.620 --> 17:46.610
[Seasons Change Hostel]

17:41.200 --> 17:42.510
What? What are you doing?

17:42.510 --> 17:43.420
Pay up.

17:45.140 --> 17:46.940
How much did we agree on earlier?

17:47.480 --> 17:48.880
Didn't we already agree?

17:49.030 --> 17:50.230
It was such a long way.

17:50.270 --> 17:50.900
Five yuan.

17:51.090 --> 17:57.420
[Seasons Change Hostel]

17:55.030 --> 17:55.460
Sir,

17:55.960 --> 17:57.420
my name is Cao Ye.

17:58.200 --> 17:59.140
I'm a painter.

18:00.110 --> 18:02.070
You saw for yourself where I brought

18:02.070 --> 18:03.330
these paintings from.

18:04.480 --> 18:05.770
I'll give you a painting.

18:05.770 --> 18:07.110
When I become famous one day,

18:07.110 --> 18:09.240
that painting will be worth a fortune.

18:09.240 --> 18:10.530
"Worth a fortune?"

18:10.550 --> 18:11.570
You can't even scrape together five yuan,

18:11.570 --> 18:13.220
and you're talking to me about fortunes?

18:13.220 --> 18:16.520
[Seasons Change Hostel]

18:13.570 --> 18:14.770
What's all the noise?

18:17.700 --> 18:18.900
What's going on here?

18:22.570 --> 18:24.570
You're moving down in the world, eh?

18:26.140 --> 18:28.340
We just turned into a dragon, didn't we?

18:29.920 --> 18:31.850
Why are you looking at me like that?

18:32.010 --> 18:32.570
Dragon.

18:35.380 --> 18:36.140
Lend me five yuan first

18:36.140 --> 18:37.240
so I can settle the fare.

18:37.240 --> 18:38.370
Put it on my room tab.

18:38.660 --> 18:40.010
Well, when you left,

18:40.010 --> 18:41.050
I paid 30 yuan

18:41.070 --> 18:41.980
for your taxi!

18:42.240 --> 18:44.060
Now you want another five yuan?

18:44.940 --> 18:45.940
I have other gigs out there,

18:45.940 --> 18:46.610
you know that.

18:46.610 --> 18:48.420
I'll pay you everything once I get paid.

18:48.420 --> 18:49.400
Mr. Cao,

18:49.420 --> 18:50.500
how much rent do you owe—

18:50.500 --> 18:52.110
don't you have a clue yourself?

18:52.110 --> 18:53.350
You keep saying, "Pay me everything."

18:53.350 --> 18:54.850
But when are you actually going to pay me?

18:54.850 --> 18:56.220
Tomorrow. I'll definitely pay tomorrow.

18:56.220 --> 18:57.610
You keep saying "tomorrow!"

18:57.610 --> 18:58.940
Can I even count on that?

18:59.920 --> 19:00.770
If you two want to argue,

19:00.770 --> 19:01.990
go do it inside.

19:02.270 --> 19:03.530
I've been standing here waiting forever.

19:03.530 --> 19:04.900
Don't you try to take advantage of
an honest man!

19:04.900 --> 19:05.830
Hurry up and pay!

19:08.180 --> 19:09.180
Northeasterner,

19:11.240 --> 19:12.170
I'm begging you.

19:12.740 --> 19:13.960
I mean, you two grown men

19:13.960 --> 19:15.200
don't have five yuan?

19:17.660 --> 19:18.350
We'll pay!

19:18.750 --> 19:20.610
It's just five yuan! I'll pay you!

19:23.700 --> 19:25.030
When Cui approached me,

19:25.110 --> 19:26.030
I considered it

19:27.460 --> 19:29.190
and finally agreed to meet you.

19:29.310 --> 19:30.180
Mainly because

19:30.440 --> 19:31.370
there are things

19:31.400 --> 19:32.530
I want to explain

19:32.790 --> 19:33.720
to you in person.

19:33.830 --> 19:35.480
Are you talking about that role?

19:35.480 --> 19:36.700
Director Cui told me.

19:36.850 --> 19:38.420
He said you're the investor

19:38.460 --> 19:39.390
in this project.

19:39.460 --> 19:40.120
One of them.

19:41.110 --> 19:42.510
I'm one of the investors.

19:44.570 --> 19:45.900
I'll be honest with you.

19:46.290 --> 19:47.500
Even though I'm an investor

19:47.500 --> 19:48.230
in this show,

19:48.720 --> 19:50.120
when it comes to casting,

19:50.440 --> 19:51.440
I don't have a say.

19:51.960 --> 19:53.290
How does that saying go?

19:53.530 --> 19:54.330
"Leave professional matters

19:54.330 --> 19:55.700
to professionals."

19:56.590 --> 19:57.700
As for casting,

19:57.900 --> 19:59.880
we have to let the director handle it.

19:59.880 --> 20:00.460
In short,

20:00.480 --> 20:01.810
what I'm trying to say is

20:01.940 --> 20:04.220
that everything is
for the sake of the show.

20:04.220 --> 20:06.110
Good casting makes a good show.

20:06.570 --> 20:07.220
A good show

20:07.610 --> 20:08.940
means we all make money.

20:09.240 --> 20:10.270
You see, these days,

20:10.270 --> 20:11.010
no one would let

20:11.010 --> 20:12.270
personal preferences

20:12.660 --> 20:13.900
tank their own production

20:13.900 --> 20:15.400
and lose money, right?

20:17.110 --> 20:17.680
Right.

20:18.310 --> 20:19.250
You're right.

20:20.920 --> 20:21.660
But before,

20:21.770 --> 20:22.770
Director Cui did cast me

20:22.770 --> 20:23.810
in that role.

20:25.110 --> 20:27.240
Now that I've been suddenly replaced,

20:27.400 --> 20:29.400
I can't help feeling upset about it.

20:30.250 --> 20:31.050
I understand.

20:32.140 --> 20:34.000
Replacing actors before filming

20:34.140 --> 20:34.940
isn't common,

20:35.420 --> 20:36.480
but it does happen.

20:37.030 --> 20:38.630
So don't take it personally.

20:39.720 --> 20:40.480
Maybe because that was my

20:40.480 --> 20:41.610
first opportunity,

20:42.400 --> 20:43.460
it meant a lot to me.

20:46.350 --> 20:48.550
That was your first opportunity, true.

20:48.790 --> 20:50.320
But it can't be the only one.

20:50.810 --> 20:51.330
You see,

20:52.030 --> 20:53.270
an actress like you—

20:53.550 --> 20:54.200
young,

20:54.500 --> 20:55.980
with little life experience

20:55.980 --> 20:57.640
and no connections to speak of—

20:57.640 --> 21:00.100
really does need someone
to give her a leg up.

21:00.400 --> 21:01.260
How about this?

21:01.550 --> 21:02.410
I'll do my best.

21:04.920 --> 21:06.520
If you're willing to help me,

21:07.220 --> 21:08.750
I'd be extremely grateful.

21:08.770 --> 21:10.140
Don't thank me yet.

21:10.740 --> 21:11.940
When I saw your headshot,

21:11.940 --> 21:13.070
I thought to myself,

21:13.250 --> 21:14.450
such a beautiful girl

21:14.610 --> 21:15.880
is bound to make it big sooner or later

21:15.880 --> 21:16.960
in this industry.

21:17.420 --> 21:19.140
I'd better watch myself around you now—

21:19.140 --> 21:20.240
can't afford to get on your bad side.

21:20.240 --> 21:21.850
If you become a star one day

21:22.070 --> 21:23.010
and badmouth me in the industry,

21:23.010 --> 21:24.870
I wouldn't be able to handle that.

21:30.830 --> 21:37.540
[Public Phone; Long-Distance Service]

21:31.200 --> 21:31.750
Mr. Lyu.

21:32.070 --> 21:33.270
Yeah, yeah. I'm good.

21:33.660 --> 21:34.720
You doing well too?

21:36.830 --> 21:38.830
Well... there's just a small thing.

21:39.070 --> 21:41.830
Well, I recently took on a gig,

21:41.850 --> 21:43.450
but they haven't paid me yet.

21:43.660 --> 21:45.390
So I was wondering if I could...

21:46.240 --> 21:48.110
borrow 50 from you first.

21:48.850 --> 21:49.790
Once I get paid for this gig,

21:49.790 --> 21:50.990
I'll immediately...

21:51.480 --> 21:52.080
Mr. Lyu...

21:52.160 --> 21:52.570
Hello?

21:58.140 --> 22:04.220
[Public Phone; Long-Distance Service]

22:15.700 --> 22:16.400
Zhao?

22:17.850 --> 22:19.160
Zhao, Mr. Zhao!

22:20.030 --> 22:21.000
It's me, Cao Ye.

22:23.010 --> 22:24.870
Suddenly thought of you? Come on!

22:25.110 --> 22:26.290
I've always been thinking of you.

22:26.290 --> 22:27.400
Not just now.

22:29.440 --> 22:31.240
No, n-nothing serious. Just...

22:32.350 --> 22:34.220
I took on a gig recently,

22:34.880 --> 22:36.220
but haven't gotten paid yet.

22:36.220 --> 22:37.010
I'm a bit tight on cash.

22:37.010 --> 22:38.610
I was wondering if I could...

22:38.750 --> 22:40.550
borrow 30 from you first.

22:43.350 --> 22:44.290
Had a surgery?

22:45.440 --> 22:46.250
When did that happen?

22:46.250 --> 22:47.850
Wait, what... what illness?

22:48.900 --> 22:49.830
Mr. Zhao, you...

22:50.900 --> 22:51.560
Mr. Zhao...

22:54.020 --> 22:58.870
[Public Phone; Long-Distance Service]

22:59.420 --> 23:00.950
Just leave the money there.

23:04.380 --> 23:04.940
What?

23:05.350 --> 23:06.770
Don't tell me you didn't bring any money.

23:06.770 --> 23:07.400
I... I...

23:08.270 --> 23:10.400
Keep calling if you haven't finished yet.

23:10.400 --> 23:10.810
Yeah.

23:15.880 --> 23:17.490
W-When I came here,

23:17.720 --> 23:19.400
my shoes kept slipping off.

23:19.440 --> 23:20.370
My shoelaces...

23:30.850 --> 23:32.220
Room and board included.

23:32.220 --> 23:33.750
Would you like to join

23:33.750 --> 23:34.900
our big family?

25:05.850 --> 25:07.310
It's enough. It's enough!

25:14.850 --> 25:15.250
Dad.

25:16.350 --> 25:17.080
Don't worry.

25:17.980 --> 25:18.940
With my skills,

25:19.880 --> 25:22.880
I'll definitely
make something of myself in Beijing.

25:26.460 --> 25:28.390
Just take care of yourself at home.

25:28.400 --> 25:30.330
Wait for me to bring you to Beijing.

26:01.380 --> 26:01.910
Alright.

26:05.200 --> 26:05.800
This is it.

26:48.940 --> 26:50.070
Knife-cut noodles!

26:51.030 --> 26:52.140
Cao, what...

26:57.110 --> 26:57.750
Cao?

27:19.180 --> 27:21.350
Cao... What happened?

27:23.500 --> 27:24.550
This afternoon,

27:24.960 --> 27:25.530
he hauled back

27:25.530 --> 27:26.660
all those paintings

27:26.660 --> 27:27.640
he'd taken out to sell

27:27.640 --> 27:29.700
and asked me
to find a place to store them.

27:29.700 --> 27:30.480
I just finished

27:30.480 --> 27:31.810
helping him put everything away,

27:31.810 --> 27:33.000
and when I came back, he was gone.

27:33.000 --> 27:33.660
Well, he...

27:33.720 --> 27:36.000
He didn't even s-say goodbye?

27:36.310 --> 27:37.370
He still owes rent.

27:38.030 --> 27:39.760
And I even covered his cab fare.

27:40.920 --> 27:42.180
He really is a heretic.

27:45.570 --> 27:48.170
At least he had the conscience
to make noodles.

27:57.570 --> 28:00.770
Oh, ocean, ocean...

28:01.680 --> 28:03.210
What's with these noodles?

28:04.530 --> 28:05.140
Cao.

28:10.750 --> 28:11.210
Well...

28:11.960 --> 28:12.820
Where did he go?

28:13.070 --> 28:13.570
No idea.

28:14.680 --> 28:15.740
Just made everyone

28:16.740 --> 28:18.340
a bowl of knife-cut noodles.

28:22.960 --> 28:23.890
Let's eat, then.

28:25.050 --> 28:26.710
Or the noodles will get soggy.

28:27.050 --> 28:27.780
You go ahead.

28:29.140 --> 28:30.600
I don't have the appetite.

29:06.090 --> 29:07.160
You made noodles.

29:08.500 --> 29:09.320
Great.

29:09.570 --> 29:11.250
So nice to come home to a meal waiting.

29:11.250 --> 29:12.200
Cao Ye made them.

29:15.740 --> 29:16.540
What's wrong?

29:17.530 --> 29:18.740
Cao Ye left.

29:19.720 --> 29:20.640
He made a bowl of noodles for each of us

29:20.640 --> 29:21.550
before he went.

29:36.880 --> 29:37.810
Are you alright?

29:39.090 --> 29:41.510
You won't leave, will you?

29:41.960 --> 29:42.790
No, I won't.

29:44.110 --> 29:45.510
There, there. Don't cry.

30:09.080 --> 30:18.230
[Seasons Change Hostel]

30:23.530 --> 30:25.070
Ma'am, a steamer of buns

30:25.070 --> 30:26.030
and a bowl of soybean milk.

30:26.030 --> 30:26.960
Coming right up.

30:33.850 --> 30:35.030
Meat or vegetarian?

30:35.160 --> 30:35.550
Meat.

30:37.510 --> 30:38.190
Mr. Xu?

30:38.750 --> 30:39.610
Zhuang Zhuang?

30:39.830 --> 30:40.630
Just got back?

30:40.980 --> 30:42.380
Where are you going so early?

30:42.380 --> 30:43.090
Going to class.

30:43.090 --> 30:43.970
Have you eaten?

30:44.160 --> 30:44.610
No.

30:44.880 --> 30:46.480
Then sit down and eat with me.

30:49.140 --> 30:50.640
Come on, it won't take long.

30:50.640 --> 30:51.970
Come on, sit. Have some.

30:52.960 --> 30:53.310
Okay.

30:54.140 --> 30:54.830
Ma'am,

30:55.000 --> 30:55.610
one more steamer of buns

30:55.610 --> 30:56.200
and a bowl of soybean milk.

30:56.200 --> 30:56.800
Coming up.

30:59.980 --> 31:01.000
Give it to her first.

31:01.000 --> 31:01.640
Thank you.

31:03.500 --> 31:05.300
Why is your class so early today?

31:05.780 --> 31:06.590
Recently, Mr. Zheng

31:06.590 --> 31:08.380
has only had time in the mornings.

31:08.380 --> 31:10.780
And I have to get up early
to warm up my voice.

31:13.500 --> 31:14.530
Okay, thanks.

31:15.380 --> 31:16.850
How are your lessons going?

31:16.850 --> 31:18.180
Pulled an all-nighter?

31:19.250 --> 31:20.220
Mr. He says

31:21.180 --> 31:22.780
inspiration is like a ghost—

31:22.870 --> 31:24.160
you never know when it'll come,

31:24.160 --> 31:25.240
and it's fleeting.

31:25.440 --> 31:27.240
So I have to grab hold of it tight.

31:31.880 --> 31:33.140
If I hadn't called you,

31:33.180 --> 31:34.810
you'd really have skipped breakfast?

31:34.810 --> 31:35.660
That won't do.

31:36.900 --> 31:38.070
You need to eat properly

31:38.070 --> 31:39.330
before going to class.

31:49.310 --> 31:51.290
Have you been coming back
at this time every day?

31:51.290 --> 31:52.020
Pretty much.

31:54.940 --> 31:55.540
All yours.

31:56.000 --> 31:56.690
I'm full.

31:56.770 --> 31:58.200
You're eating that little?

31:58.200 --> 31:59.480
Have a few more.

31:59.810 --> 32:02.740
Play on a full stomach,
sing on an empty one—you know?

32:04.090 --> 32:06.220
I think I've heard that saying before.

32:09.400 --> 32:09.960
In the future,

32:09.960 --> 32:11.760
we can have breakfast together.

32:12.030 --> 32:12.820
Sure!

32:14.050 --> 32:14.780
Sounds good!

32:15.310 --> 32:16.090
Perfect—I can't eat that much

32:16.090 --> 32:17.270
in the morning anyway.

32:17.270 --> 32:17.900
If we eat together,

32:17.900 --> 32:18.830
you can help me finish it.

32:18.830 --> 32:19.370
Sure!

32:19.640 --> 32:21.070
T-Then let's set a time?

32:22.610 --> 32:23.330
Half past six?

32:23.330 --> 32:24.200
-Okay.
-Good.

32:25.250 --> 32:26.610
From now on,

32:26.660 --> 32:28.660
one steamer is enough for both of us.

32:28.900 --> 32:29.830
You need to eat more.

32:29.830 --> 32:31.090
You're still growing.

32:31.400 --> 32:33.290
Me? Still growing?

32:33.490 --> 32:34.330
Look how old I am.

32:34.330 --> 32:35.350
I'm done growing.

32:35.460 --> 32:37.460
One steamer is just right—no waste.

32:37.530 --> 32:37.920
Fine.

32:39.590 --> 32:40.070
See?

32:40.090 --> 32:41.420
You pop them in one bite.

32:41.660 --> 32:43.110
Yes, one bite.

32:43.140 --> 32:45.140
Still, I can't finish two steamers.

32:46.570 --> 32:48.300
Can you eat one in a single bite?

32:48.330 --> 32:49.660
I can only have two buns.

32:49.940 --> 32:52.470
Play on a full stomach
and sing on an empty one.

32:53.140 --> 32:54.800
Here, Miss, raise your glass!

32:55.140 --> 32:56.240
Come on, cheers!

32:56.310 --> 32:57.870
Come on! Raise your glass!

32:58.270 --> 32:58.720
Right.

32:59.030 --> 32:59.620
Clink!

33:04.010 --> 33:04.840
Good, good.

33:04.960 --> 33:06.510
Come on, let's have another one!

33:06.510 --> 33:07.380
Mr. Wang, Mr. Wang.

33:07.380 --> 33:08.030
Come on.

33:08.380 --> 33:10.070
Don't just focus on Ranran.

33:10.110 --> 33:11.570
Have one with me, will you?

33:12.220 --> 33:13.440
Let's have one together!

33:13.440 --> 33:14.790
You can't neglect me
for a pretty face, right?

33:14.790 --> 33:15.690
I'll drink with you!

33:15.690 --> 33:16.150
Cheers!

33:16.210 --> 33:16.670
Cheers!

33:17.510 --> 33:18.230
Thanks.

33:20.310 --> 33:20.920
Miss,

33:21.700 --> 33:23.160
raise your glass. Together!

33:23.160 --> 33:24.220
What's wrong?

33:24.510 --> 33:24.960
Come on.

33:24.960 --> 33:25.880
Bottoms up, bottoms up.

33:25.880 --> 33:26.830
-Mr. Wang.
-Look at you.

33:26.830 --> 33:27.360
Mr. Wang!

33:27.500 --> 33:28.230
Listen to me.

33:28.750 --> 33:29.610
Our Ranran here

33:29.980 --> 33:31.550
is an absolutely great actress.

33:31.550 --> 33:32.900
Last time, due to scheduling conflicts,

33:32.900 --> 33:34.500
she had to miss out on my show.

33:34.980 --> 33:35.750
Aren't you currently

33:35.750 --> 33:37.220
investing in a new production?

33:37.220 --> 33:37.900
I've looked into it.

33:37.900 --> 33:39.510
The production scale is decent.

33:39.510 --> 33:41.090
You shouldn't miss out on her again.

33:41.090 --> 33:43.080
We need to use a good actress like her!

33:43.080 --> 33:43.790
I'm telling you—

33:43.790 --> 33:45.640
I'm sharing a gem,
and it pains me to do so.

33:45.640 --> 33:46.770
If it weren't for our relationship,

33:46.770 --> 33:47.850
I wouldn't introduce her to you at all.

33:47.850 --> 33:48.780
You understand?

33:49.790 --> 33:51.010
I get it. I get it.

33:53.050 --> 33:53.880
Come on, miss.

33:54.720 --> 33:55.500
Have another cup.

33:55.500 --> 33:56.330
Mr. Wang, Mr. Wang,

33:56.330 --> 33:56.970
listen to me.

33:56.970 --> 33:58.100
I haven't finished.

33:59.010 --> 33:59.550
I'm telling you,

33:59.550 --> 34:00.460
young actors

34:00.480 --> 34:01.400
like her

34:01.590 --> 34:02.810
are just like grass.

34:03.440 --> 34:05.460
As long as people like us
give them more water

34:05.460 --> 34:06.520
and more sunlight,

34:07.240 --> 34:09.100
sooner or later, they will bloom.

34:11.550 --> 34:13.280
Mr. Chu, that metaphor of yours

34:13.360 --> 34:14.730
is really something.

34:15.030 --> 34:15.850
Sunshine.

34:16.570 --> 34:17.969
Grass.

34:19.170 --> 34:21.030
Let me take a look at this "grass."

34:21.480 --> 34:22.870
Take a look. Go ahead.

34:32.340 --> 34:34.000
This "grass" looks...

34:34.400 --> 34:35.130
pretty good.

34:36.190 --> 34:37.250
It's just...

34:37.590 --> 34:39.150
I wonder how her acting is.

34:39.210 --> 34:39.810
Good!

34:39.980 --> 34:41.040
Her acting is good.

34:41.130 --> 34:41.989
How do you know?

34:42.000 --> 34:43.280
There isn't even a script.

34:43.280 --> 34:44.420
Well, how about this?

34:44.420 --> 34:47.090
How about letting her show us a talent?

34:48.460 --> 34:49.190
Show us a talent?

34:49.190 --> 34:50.389
You... Aren't you...

34:50.420 --> 34:51.190
Well, Wang,

34:51.360 --> 34:51.820
you...

34:51.960 --> 34:53.320
Is that really necessary?

34:53.320 --> 34:54.710
Don't you trust my judgment?

34:54.710 --> 34:55.889
Trust me on this.

34:56.840 --> 34:58.370
I've got things to do today.

34:58.500 --> 34:59.560
Let's call it a day.

35:00.550 --> 35:01.410
Check, please!

35:01.530 --> 35:02.170
Waiter!

35:02.320 --> 35:03.430
Over here! Waiter!

35:05.970 --> 35:06.790
I can dance.

35:08.860 --> 35:09.600
I can dance.

35:10.730 --> 35:11.170
Good.

35:12.070 --> 35:13.470
If you want to be a star,

35:13.670 --> 35:15.330
you've got to have that drive!

35:15.880 --> 35:16.510
Yes, yes.

35:23.920 --> 35:24.940
Good! Good!

36:17.070 --> 36:17.920
Bravo! Bravo!

36:18.000 --> 36:18.860
Bravo! Bravo!

36:18.960 --> 36:20.630
Now that's a one-in-a-million talent!

36:20.630 --> 36:21.920
A talent. I told you!

36:28.210 --> 36:28.940
Let's drink.

36:29.190 --> 36:29.760
Cheers.

36:41.320 --> 36:42.100
Where is she?

36:42.420 --> 36:43.350
Why has she gone?

36:46.950 --> 36:49.220
She's just so cute.

37:22.090 --> 37:23.950
Come on, I'll walk you to the door.

37:25.590 --> 37:27.420
Mrs. Zheng, I'm leaving now.

37:27.510 --> 37:28.440
Leaving so soon?

37:28.570 --> 37:29.530
Then I won't see you out.

37:29.530 --> 37:30.260
That's fine.

37:30.920 --> 37:31.980
You must remember.

37:32.570 --> 37:34.420
Take good care of your voice.

37:34.510 --> 37:34.980
Mr. Zheng.

37:34.980 --> 37:35.420
If...

37:36.110 --> 37:36.530
What is this?

37:36.530 --> 37:38.090
Thank you for your help last time.

37:38.090 --> 37:39.980
I told you, there's no hurry.

37:40.010 --> 37:43.210
-I must pay you back.
-The meal is ready. Zhuang Zhuang...

37:47.960 --> 37:49.070
What's this about?

37:49.400 --> 37:50.330
Explain it to me.

37:51.260 --> 37:53.660
It's Zhuang Zhuang's... tuition.

37:53.710 --> 37:55.170
Didn't she already pay it?

37:56.380 --> 37:57.900
I paid for her.

37:58.070 --> 38:00.070
Well, aren't you something, Zheng.

38:00.210 --> 38:01.440
You teach her

38:01.480 --> 38:03.610
and cover her tuition on top of it, huh?

38:04.460 --> 38:05.500
What are you after?

38:05.500 --> 38:06.900
I told you already.

38:07.000 --> 38:09.260
When Zhuang Zhuang first came to Beijing,

38:09.260 --> 38:10.800
her wallet was stolen.

38:10.900 --> 38:12.500
She didn't have money for tuition,

38:12.500 --> 38:14.380
so she had to work part-time to
earn money.

38:14.380 --> 38:15.170
Because she didn't have the money,

38:15.170 --> 38:16.550
you paid out of your own pocket?

38:16.550 --> 38:17.570
Well, if I didn't,

38:17.690 --> 38:18.150
what...

38:19.050 --> 38:19.630
what would she do?

38:19.630 --> 38:21.030
You could have told me!

38:21.090 --> 38:22.340
Like I have the guts.

38:22.650 --> 38:23.580
You didn't dare?

38:23.610 --> 38:24.230
Am I really

38:24.260 --> 38:25.660
an unreasonable person?

38:26.940 --> 38:28.380
Come clean right now.

38:28.570 --> 38:29.960
You've been keeping a secret stash.

38:29.960 --> 38:31.650
Since when?

38:31.840 --> 38:32.670
And how much is left?

38:32.670 --> 38:33.690
Where have you been hiding it?

38:33.690 --> 38:35.530
You're telling me everything today!

38:35.530 --> 38:37.650
Are you trying to blow up this marriage?

38:37.650 --> 38:38.920
Watch your words.

38:38.940 --> 38:40.210
-Watch what?
-Why do you have to say it so nastily?

38:40.210 --> 38:41.090
How is it nasty?

38:41.190 --> 38:42.150
My words are nasty?

38:42.150 --> 38:43.860
Isn't what you did nasty?

38:44.030 --> 38:45.530
You have to admit it!

38:45.940 --> 38:47.430
Zheng, I'm telling you—

38:47.480 --> 38:48.880
whatever else you're hiding from me,

38:48.880 --> 38:50.650
you'd better come clean today!

38:50.760 --> 38:52.760
Otherwise, there'll be hell to pay!

38:55.000 --> 38:55.590
Zongbao,

38:56.110 --> 38:57.210
tell me...

38:58.920 --> 39:00.400
Where could Cao have gone?

39:01.260 --> 39:02.880
How's he doing now?

39:06.550 --> 39:08.110
Let's think positively.

39:09.800 --> 39:10.420
Cao...

39:12.610 --> 39:13.810
has gone to Xinjiang.

39:14.380 --> 39:15.670
To gather inspiration

39:15.800 --> 39:16.880
and paint.

39:17.260 --> 39:19.300
To see the snow-capped mountains

39:19.630 --> 39:21.090
and the grasslands there.

39:21.230 --> 39:22.150
Maybe,

39:22.230 --> 39:23.940
in Dabancheng,

39:24.500 --> 39:25.430
he'll meet a girl

39:25.800 --> 39:27.980
and fall head over heels.

39:28.690 --> 39:29.510
Next year,

39:29.820 --> 39:31.750
he'll come back to our room, right?

39:32.090 --> 39:33.210
With a kid along.

39:35.300 --> 39:35.960
I hope so.

39:37.290 --> 39:38.430
Best wishes to him.

39:38.980 --> 39:40.180
Xu, what do you think?

39:44.550 --> 39:45.800
Xu, why are you so quiet?

39:45.800 --> 39:47.730
Thinking about the one in Room 116?

39:47.840 --> 39:49.690
No, I'm pondering a scene.

39:49.860 --> 39:50.660
What scene?

39:50.940 --> 39:51.740
What scene?

39:53.030 --> 39:55.170
Mr. He described a scene.

39:56.070 --> 39:57.170
It was really good.

39:57.550 --> 39:57.920
See?

39:58.610 --> 39:59.690
He's got serious work.

39:59.690 --> 40:01.260
Yeah, he described it well.

40:01.280 --> 40:02.810
Why did you pull a long face?

40:03.050 --> 40:04.230
But I just feel...

40:05.000 --> 40:06.590
there's a better way to handle it.

40:06.590 --> 40:07.570
Then tell him

40:07.590 --> 40:08.400
your ideas.

40:10.170 --> 40:11.630
That... That won't do.

40:12.170 --> 40:13.880
We call him the great screenwriter,

40:13.880 --> 40:16.980
but that title only counts

40:16.980 --> 40:17.920
within these four walls.

40:17.920 --> 40:19.180
When you're out there,

40:19.230 --> 40:21.000
you have to keep your head down,

40:21.010 --> 40:21.510
am I right?

40:21.510 --> 40:24.010
You can't go around
giving your mentor advice.

40:24.010 --> 40:24.870
Remember that.

40:26.880 --> 40:27.960
Little Northeasterner

40:27.960 --> 40:29.090
told me the other day

40:29.170 --> 40:30.230
that when Cao left,

40:30.280 --> 40:31.480
he still owed rent.

40:32.360 --> 40:33.190
And on top of that,

40:33.190 --> 40:34.650
Cao owed him some cab fare.

40:35.230 --> 40:36.210
We've all lived together

40:36.210 --> 40:37.150
for so long.

40:37.190 --> 40:38.510
We have a bond.

40:39.210 --> 40:41.330
We can't let Cao's name

40:41.460 --> 40:43.060
get tarnished in the hostel.

40:43.820 --> 40:44.860
I say we do this—

40:45.280 --> 40:47.030
the three of us chip in some money

40:47.030 --> 40:47.760
and pay off

40:47.860 --> 40:48.420
his debt.

40:48.960 --> 40:49.960
What do you think?

40:50.090 --> 40:51.280
We pay?

40:52.420 --> 40:53.880
You tell Northeasterner—

40:53.980 --> 40:55.690
a small loss can lead to a bigger gain.

40:55.690 --> 40:56.150
Well...

40:56.530 --> 40:57.730
Zongbao,

40:58.070 --> 40:59.600
we've been living together

40:59.610 --> 41:00.780
for so long.

41:01.010 --> 41:03.270
Why is it that when money comes up, you...

41:05.860 --> 41:07.120
That man here is right.

41:07.260 --> 41:09.320
A small loss can lead to a bigger gain.

41:09.400 --> 41:10.060
Who are you?

41:11.590 --> 41:12.380
I'm telling you,

41:12.380 --> 41:14.320
a small loss really can
lead to a bigger gain.

41:14.320 --> 41:15.920
Sometimes when you take a loss,

41:15.920 --> 41:17.500
the other person remembers your kindness.

41:17.500 --> 41:18.590
Who knows—one day,

41:18.760 --> 41:20.090
they might repay your small kindness

41:20.090 --> 41:20.960
a hundredfold!

41:21.210 --> 41:21.880
By then...

41:22.730 --> 41:24.000
you'll come out way ahead,

41:24.000 --> 41:24.460
right?

41:24.510 --> 41:25.260
Well, why are you here?

41:25.260 --> 41:25.920
Who is this?

41:27.340 --> 41:28.500
You sure make yourself at home
with strangers.

41:28.500 --> 41:30.230
Well, it just kind of happened.

41:30.630 --> 41:31.230
Everyone,

41:32.750 --> 41:34.080
Comrade Cao Ye has gone.

41:34.550 --> 41:35.690
Just like that—he left us

41:35.690 --> 41:36.380
quietly.

41:36.510 --> 41:38.260
Are you delivering a eulogy or what?

41:38.260 --> 41:39.460
Who is this?

41:40.960 --> 41:41.760
Cao Ye left,

41:42.380 --> 41:43.980
but his bed can't stay empty.

41:44.360 --> 41:45.010
Around here,

41:45.010 --> 41:46.420
every spot has to be filled.

41:46.420 --> 41:48.150
From now on, this gentleman here

41:48.150 --> 41:49.160
is joining us.

41:49.530 --> 41:50.050
His name is...

41:50.050 --> 41:50.510
Xiaobo.

41:51.280 --> 41:53.030
I'm Li Xiaobo!

41:55.050 --> 41:55.690
Everyone,

41:55.780 --> 41:57.420
let's get close from now on.

41:57.730 --> 41:58.840
Let's look out for each other.

41:58.840 --> 41:59.780
Come on, make way.

41:59.780 --> 42:01.090
Let's get close!

42:01.940 --> 42:03.320
Let's share the blessings.

42:03.320 --> 42:04.300
Come on, come on.

42:04.650 --> 42:05.630
Let's share the blessings.

42:05.630 --> 42:06.370
No, no, no.

42:06.630 --> 42:07.090
I get it.

42:07.670 --> 42:08.780
And share the hardships too.

42:08.780 --> 42:09.610
Here, take this.

42:09.610 --> 42:10.500
No, no, no.

42:10.590 --> 42:11.920
That's not what I meant.

42:12.230 --> 42:13.690
And share the hardships too.

42:13.690 --> 42:15.530
Let's share the blessings
and the hardships.

42:15.530 --> 42:16.550
As for me,

42:17.340 --> 42:18.920
I go to bed early and get up early.

42:18.920 --> 42:20.120
If I ever disturb you,

42:20.880 --> 42:22.010
please bear with me!

42:22.460 --> 42:23.590
Please bear with me.

42:25.170 --> 42:26.230
It's getting late.

42:26.300 --> 42:26.760
Give me.

42:29.880 --> 42:30.680
Time to sleep!

42:37.360 --> 42:37.960
Go to sleep.

42:37.960 --> 42:38.420
Come on.

42:38.730 --> 42:39.190
Come on.

42:39.630 --> 42:40.830
I need to make the bed.

42:42.460 --> 42:42.990
Alright.

42:43.610 --> 42:44.410
Time to sleep!

42:49.210 --> 42:49.810
It's okay.

42:50.170 --> 42:51.430
You guys keep talking.

42:51.900 --> 42:52.900
I had a long day today.
